<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Political Adviser in Korea (
                        Jacobs
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d575</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">575</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-08-18T21:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-08-18T21:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-18T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-18T21:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895.00/8–1747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jacobs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-18T22:00:00-04:00">August 18, 1947—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. State Dept working group, formed to prepare Korean case for submission to
                    UN, in implementing annex to Appendix D, <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0770" n="756" xml:id="pg_756"/> 176/30 is considering procedure
                    whereby Four Powers, under Article 10 of UN Charter will request <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> to provide UN observers of elections in Korea. It
                    is believed observers should arrive in Korea well in advance of first elections
                    and it is contemplated that US will provide transportation and housing to group
                    in its zone. Your recommendations as to approximate number needed and comments
                    as to best methods of operation will be appreciated.</p>
                <p>While Dept agrees that preparation for election in US zone in near future should
                    be continued (<gloss target="#t_PolAd1">PolAd</gloss>’s 279<note n="72" xml:id="d575fn72">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>) in view steps outlined annex to
                    Appendix D <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss> 176/30, it is believed no
                    date for such election should be decided upon or announced until receipt further
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
